Not only did we literally receive the bill before it arrived, she was terribly unhappy with the seafood quality and flavor.
Her Diet Coke didn't show up till the end either - producing more sour reviews on her part.
My "veggie soup" consisted of a piece of broccoli, three carrots and an onion slice soaked in wonton broth.
Go with the egg drop instead.
I will mention that we were already grossly disappointed having learned the Golden Buddha was closed and it's hard to compete with them.
For a quick, low budget Chinese food experience with a decent ambiance, Szechwan Palace is an option, but not a GREAT one.

