I got lunch to go, ordered the lemon chicken and crab puffs.
The chicken was delicious, the rice (I got fried) wasn't too greasy and it came with a salad, your choice of soup, and egg roll.
The salad surprised me, but it was pretty mediocre.
I got the egg drop soup and while the portion was not as large as other places, they made up for it in quality.
They are generous with the eggs and with the veggies that are in there.
I love that they don't use green onions too (HATE green onions).
The portion sizes are consistent with lunch-sized portions; pretty much what you'd expect.
The crab puffs are absolutely delicious.
I hate when I get crab puffs somewhere and they don't have crab or the cream cheese is cold OR they put too many onions in them.
This place has them down perfectly; not too oniony and the perfect crispiness.
It was inexpensive and super tasty; I can't complain.

