Every restaurant I've been to near an Asian market is fantastic and this is no exception.
When we entered the place was packed which is always nice to see.
The menu was huge which normally I don't like but this place has a great reason behind it - they offer traditional Chinese and Americanized dishes as well and they separate it on the menu too.
We leaned more towards the American side since it was our first time.
The pork fried rice was killer -the tables favorite.
The chow mein was next in line and we got just the veggie version.
